    contentEn: 
`<h2>What is a Drape Curtain?</h2>
<p>A drape curtain (fon perde) is a thick or medium-thick curtain type used on both sides of the window for decorative and functional purposes, usually complementing sheer curtains. Drape curtains add color, texture, and depth to the space. It is also preferred to provide privacy in the evening hours, reduce sunlight, or create decorative integrity.</p>
<p>Drape curtains create a strong character in home decoration. When correctly chosen, it can make the living room look more luxurious, the bedroom more peaceful, and the sitting room warmer.</p>

<h2>Where are Drape Curtains Used?</h2>
<p>Drape curtains are most commonly used in the living room, bedroom, and sitting room. It stands out as a complementary part of decoration in living rooms. In bedrooms, it is preferred for privacy and light control. On large glass areas, drape curtains give the space a more balanced and finished look.</p>
<p>Drape curtains are also frequently used in hotel rooms, villa decorations, office executive rooms, and specially designed areas.</p>

<h2>How to Choose Drape Curtain Fabric?</h2>
<p>When choosing drape curtain fabric, decoration style, purpose of use, and the light-receiving status of the room should be considered. Linen-textured drapes offer a natural and simple look. Velvet drapes create a luxurious and showy atmosphere. Blackout fabric drapes provide light control.</p>
<p>More decorative fabrics can be preferred in living rooms. In the bedroom, fabrics that reduce light and provide privacy are more suitable. Easy-to-clean and safe fabrics should be chosen in children's rooms.</p>

<h2>How to Choose Drape Curtain Color?</h2>
<p>Drape curtain color strongly affects the general mood of the room. Light tones provide a more spacious and calm look. Dark tones create a more sophisticated and eye-catching effect.</p>
<p>Colors such as navy blue, anthracite, emerald green, burgundy, and brown look impressive in luxury decorations. Beige, cream, stone color, and light gray tones are timeless and harmonious options.</p>
<p>When choosing drape curtains, wall, carpet, sofa, and accessory colors should be evaluated together. Integrity can be established with different shades of the same color, or a strong emphasis can be made with contrasting colors.</p>

<h2>How Long Should Drape Curtains Be?</h2>
<p>Floor-length usage in drape curtains is one of the most stylish looks. Drape curtains descending from ceiling to floor make the space look higher and elegant. The curtain slightly touching the floor provides a modern and tidy look. Curtains left very long can create a more romantic and classic effect.</p>
<p>Short drape curtains generally look weaker decoratively. Therefore, unless there is a special usage requirement, choosing long drape curtains is recommended.</p>

<h2>How to Combine Drape Curtains with Sheer Curtains?</h2>
<p>Drape curtains are generally used together with sheer curtains. If the drape curtain is intensely colored or patterned, the sheer curtain should be chosen simpler. If the sheer curtain is patterned, the drape curtain should be preferred in plain color. Thus, visual balance is preserved.</p>
<p>In modern decoration, plain sheer and plain drape curtain combination is frequently preferred. In classical decoration, embroidered sheers and rich-textured drape curtains can be used.</p>

<h2>Conclusion</h2>
<p>Drape curtains are one of the strongest curtain types that determine the character of decoration. When fabric, color, length, and sheer curtain compatibility are correctly selected, it adds elegance and depth to the space. Lale Perde makes living spaces more elegant and completed with custom-sized drape curtain solutions.</p>
`,
